 - Added depth-2 sampler-effects end-to-end test coverage (frac-0113): `tests/test_sampler_effects.py` now includes `SamplerEffectsEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `sw_sampler_fx` SuperCollider source and SC-side runtime harness through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts bus/control defaults (`in_bus=16`, `out_bus=0`, delay/reverb/freeze/comb controls), verifies the ordered integrated FX chain (`In.ar` -> `DelayC.ar` -> `FreeVerb.ar` -> `PV_Freeze` -> `CombC.ar` -> `LPF.ar` -> `Out.ar`), confirms the runtime harness compiles `sampler_effects.scd`, toggles `freeze_amount`, exercises `comb_decay` / `comb_damping`, runs `runImpulseComb`, checks the 61.74 Hz comb target, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic. `tests/test_test_sampler_effects_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing SuperCollider behavior remains unchanged because the source already produced the required one-path FX chain; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4663 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
